SPAIN DAYBOOK: Bank of Spain Published GDP Estimate

-- B y   S h a r o n   S m y t h
-- 
2011-08-05T07:28:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-05/spain-daybook-bank-of-spain-published-gdp-estimate-correct-.html
(Corrects Zapatero’s comment in third paragraph.)  The Bank of  Spain  publishes economic
growth data while the National Statistics Institute releases
industrial output figures.  WHAT TO WATCH:  *The Bank of Spain publishes figures on economic growth in
the second-quarter at 10am CET.  *Spain’s National Statistics Institute publishes Industrial
output data for June at 9 a.m. CET.  ECONOMY:  *The Spanish Treasury said in statement on its website it
will cancel a bond auction scheduled for Aug. 18 and will sell a
new five-year benchmark government note on Sept. 1.  *Prime Minister Jose Luis Rodriguez Zapatero said the
increase in Spain’s borrowing costs yesterday was
“foreseeable.”  EQUITES:  * Ferrovial SA (FER) ’s Budimex unit bought Polish railway builder
PNI for 56 million euros.  * Fersa Energias Renovables SA (FRS)  posted first-half profit of 2
million euros, reversing a 1.98 million-euro loss a year
earlier.  * Metrovacesa SA (MVC)  said it reached an agreement with lenders
to renegotiate 3.6 billion euros of debt.  MARKETS:  *The IBEX 35 Index fell 3.9 percent to 8686.5 on Aug. 4.  *The spread between Spanish and German 10-year borrowing
costs widened to 398.4 basis points.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sharon Smyth in Madrid at 
 ssmyth2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Blackman at   ablackman@bloomberg.net . 